Can't say enough good things about Murphy's! My go-to spot in Wrigleyville after work to relax, and always my #1 place to take friends & family when they're in the area. Great staff, great drinks & food, reasonable prices, and amazing atmosphere. Can't pick a favorite bartender or staff members; but I do want to give a shoutout to our first, and usual bartenders, Andy & Kate!  If you're looking for the best place to watch the Cubs game aside from Wrigley Field (especially with the pandemic going on), go to Murphy's.

I have been impressed with Murphy’s over and over again. Being this close to Wrigley field - it makes you feel like you are at the game (which is especially rare this season). The experience is unmatched. The drink selection - great. The food selection - great. But what truly makes it for me is how welcome I always feel here. It reminds me of the Cheers theme song “Sometimes you want to go, where everybody knows your name.” I love all of the bartenders/workers I’ve met here, so I’m not trying to name favorites, but I would like to give a little shout out to Lindsey. She is new to the Murphy’s family and a great addition to the team!

I just moved to the Wrigleyville area from Las Vegas and have been trying to find some good food spots around me. I’m so glad I stumbled upon Murphy’s Bleachers! Great chicken wings, fries, and the chicken caesar wrap is a must try! Huge portion sizes for reasonable prices! I’ll be back.

A review for the winter days (off-season for Cubs): Murphy's is one of the best places to hangout in the area even after the Cubs season. Their daily specials on weekdays (Fish and Chips for $6 on Fridays!!) are really good. The beer prices are very affordable in winter ($3 cans, $4-$6 monthly special drafts, etc.). A lot of space to sit and chill which would come in handy for a group looking to make last minute plans. Of course it's a popular fan-spot during the summer, Cubs season days. But I'm not that much of an baseball follower to struggle through the crowd on those days. I just prefer the winter's Murphy's.

Went here for a private event.  I have heard about Murphy's Bleachers, as it is almost legendary, and had a great time!  A must go to place if you are a true sports fan.  They have an expansive collection of Sports memorabilia, something for everyone.  This place has been here for a long time, almost 80 years.  You can come here before or after a Cubs game for a drink and some food.  But, the best time to come is on a non-game day and a big plus is if it's raining.  You will practically have the place to yourself, except for die hard regulars.  It was a rainy day when we went here, we got to walk around the whole place and take in the atmosphere without the big crowds.  On busy days, the bar in the back is less crowded, head there to avoid the traffic.  On a nice day, grab a beer, A Chicago style hot dog, sit outside or head up to the roof top and enjoy the view of beautiful Wrigley Field!
